        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Introduction"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "The Refer a Friend scheme allows employees to recommend someone they know, such as a friend or ex-colleague and receive a payment when the candidate has been successfully appointed and in post for a period of 6 months for any substantive or fixed term vacancy that is listed on the Shortage Occupation List \u2013 i.e. Hard to Fill Roles."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.2,
                "text": "NHS Employers recommend Refer a Friend Schemes to help meet workforce recruitment challenges within the NHS and schemes have been proven to help recruit into hard to fill posts and target specific occupations as required. Many of the trust are offering similar financial incentives."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.3,
                "text": "The candidate gets first-hand information about the environment, culture of the Trust and the benefits and workload of the job. If successful the new employee arrives having already had their expectations managed. They are better prepared to join the Trust than non-referred employees."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.4,
                "text": "Incentivising employees to refer candidates through a reward offer encourages them to think about who they might know that has the right skills and values and who would be a good fit for our Trust. They become ambassadors for the Trust. It also allows us to access their extensive networks."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.5,
                "text": "The Southend site currently has a Refer a Friend scheme."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Scope"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "NHS Employers recommend Refer a Friend Schemes to help meet workforce recruitment challenges within the NHS and schemes have been proven to help recruit into hard to fill posts and target specific occupations as required. Many NHS trusts are offering similar financial incentives."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.2,
                "text": "Implementation of a \u2018Refer a Friend' Scheme across Essex NHS Foundations Trust will aid in the reduction of vacancy factors and agency usage, this will intern will reduce agency expenditure."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Definitions"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 29,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 2,
                "num_cols": 2,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Term"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Definition"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Shortage Occupational List"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Hard to Fill role, any vacancy where there is a national shortage within the UK"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "Role and responsibilities within the Trust"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "It is the responsibility of recruitment to monitor application and ensure application are in line with the agree procedures."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.2,
                "text": "The workforce team are responsible for processing the \u00a3500 payments on receipt of the Contractual Change forms from recruitment."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.3,
                "text": "By signing a contractual change form, the hiring manager is agreeing that they  understand the cost involved to the department - \u00a3500"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 34,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSEGL-21034 Refer a friend scheme 1.0.003.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Terms of the scheme"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "To make a referral you must be employed on a substantive, fixed term contract with the Trust."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "All new employees referred must be offered a substantive, fixed term contract with the Trust."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "All new employees referred must have not worked at the Trust within 12 months of their current application in any capacity (e.g. substantive, Bank or Agency)."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.4,
                "text": "Family members employed by the Trust must not be placed in roles within the same department or ward as the referrer to avoid a conflict of interest."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.5,
                "text": "To meet the criteria of the scheme and receive your staff referral bonus you must complete and submit the Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust Refer a friend scheme application via a change form within 28 days of the referees start date. Forms submitted after this time period may not be valid."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.6,
                "text": "The \u00a3500 will be paid to you (the referrer) at the end of the sixth month of the new employee's employment (into hard to fill roles only)."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.7,
                "text": "There is no limit to how many claims the referring employee is entitled to claim under the Refer-A-Friend Scheme in any given calendar year."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 42
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.8,
                "text": "Referrers must be employed within the Trust to receive payment."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 43
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.9,
                "text": "Please note that payments are non-consolidated and will not count towards pension contributions, holiday pay or enhancements. Any payment made will be paid through the Trust payroll and will not subject to appropriate deductions in the normal way."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 44
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "All referred staff must have the appropriate UK registered body registration for the referee to qualify for the bonus payment: NMC, GMC etc."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 45
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.0,
                "text": "Monitoring and audit"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "Outlined below is the Trust's process of monitoring compliance with, and the effectiveness of the document's main points."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 47
        },
        {
